2.5 Compressive Creep and Shrinkage
To estimate the contribution of the compressive creep to the deformation of the beam specimens, 27 cylinders with a diameter of 104 mm were tested for a period between two weeks and four months. The tests were performed with three load levels of 0.25, 0.45 and 0.65 f[image: $$_{\mathrm {c}}$$] with a concrete age of 2, 13 and 28 days. For each combination, a sealed specimen, an unsealed specimen and a heat-treated specimen were tested.
